26
00:01:03,359 --> 00:01:04,159
You ready?

27
00:01:04,159 --> 00:01:05,120
You bet.

28
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:09,519
What is the youngest age at which children are allowed to work in the UK?

29
00:01:09,519 --> 00:01:14,159
Is it a 12, b 13 or c 14?

30
00:01:14,159 --> 00:01:16,560
Well, I'm going to say 14,

31
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:18,879
just because that's how old I was.

32
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,879
And it seems such a long time ago.

33
00:01:20,879 --> 00:01:24,640
Well, we'll find out if you're right or wrong at the end of the programme.

34
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:29,840
That let's start by hearing some British teenagers talking about their Saturday jobs.

35
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:33,760
A Saturday job is the name we give to part-time work

36
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,239
that teenagers do for extra money.

37
00:01:36,239 --> 00:01:37,840
As the name suggests,

38
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:42,719
these jobs often take place on Saturdays, but not always.

39
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:43,599
That's right.

40
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:49,040
Saturday job is a general term we use to describe part-time work done by teenagers.

41
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:52,960
The work might take place on Sundays or any day of the week, in fact.

42
00:01:52,959 --> 00:01:57,119
Let's hear from these British children about their Saturday jobs.

43
00:01:57,119 --> 00:02:00,399
We have to face all the stuff on the shelves to make it look organised

44
00:02:00,399 --> 00:02:03,119
and show customers where products are after the need to know.

45
00:02:03,119 --> 00:02:07,599
On the average week I work nine hours, so two hours for two school nights,

46
00:02:07,599 --> 00:02:10,560
and then I work four hours on a Saturday and two hours on a Sunday.

47
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:13,120
And then in their school holidays can work more,

48
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:16,159
so it's like around 16 in the school holidays.

49
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:22,560
The first teenager said the work involves making the shelves look organised.

50
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:25,280
Shop work is a very typical Saturday job.

51
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:28,800
Oh yes, I spent many a weekend and evenings stacking shelves.

52
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:34,080
The second teenager's Saturday job takes place Saturdays, Sundays and evenings.

53
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:37,439
As we said, a Saturday job is not just for Saturdays.

54
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:42,000
A Saturday job is seen almost as a right of passage in the UK.

55
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,920
A right of passage is the name we give to events or ceremonies

56
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:49,120
that form an important stage in a person's life.

57
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:52,319
That's right, like graduating from school or having children.

58
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:56,959
But according to the latest statistics in the UK, that is all changing.

59
00:02:57,519 --> 00:02:59,519
Listen to this BBC report.

60
00:02:59,519 --> 00:03:02,799
In order to work, they need a permit from the local authority.

61
00:03:02,799 --> 00:03:06,560
And our data shows the number being issued has fallen

62
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:13,840
from nearly 30,000 permits in 2012 to just 23,000 in 2016.

63
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:18,639
Employers frequently bimmone the lack of work experience young people have,

64
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:23,119
but teenagers are also facing pressure not to take up part-time jobs

65
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:25,839
and to concentrate on their studies instead.

66
00:03:27,039 --> 00:03:31,679
So, it seems that fewer teenagers are taking Saturday jobs.

67
00:03:31,679 --> 00:03:33,599
But there's a conflict here.

68
00:03:33,599 --> 00:03:38,239
Yes, on the one hand, employers bimmone the lack of work experience young people have.

69
00:03:38,799 --> 00:03:40,799
Bimmone, meaning complain about.

70
00:03:40,799 --> 00:03:42,319
It's a rather formal word.

71
00:03:42,959 --> 00:03:44,560
But on the other hand,

72
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:48,400
teenagers are facing pressure not to take part-time jobs

73
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,400
and to concentrate on their studies.

74
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:56,640
Some people think working could be detrimental to a school child's academic progress.

75
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:00,159
Detrimental, which means causing harm.

76
00:04:00,159 --> 00:04:01,439
It's a tricky one, isn't it?

77
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:05,199
I think my Saturday spent stacking shelves and serving fish and chips

78
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:10,080
taught me valuable lessons about working with adults and also managing my money.

79
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,800
I don't think it was detrimental to my education.

80
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:15,439
Well, you managed to get a job at BBC Learning English.

81
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:16,400
That's true.

82
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:20,240
As for me, my paper round taught me the value of hard work.

83
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,759
It didn't hinder me.

84
